						<div class="postbody">I'm surprised nobody has mentioned yet that IPS has several variants that are incompatible with each other, and not always possible to distinguish other than for producing erroneous output. This just makes things even worse and even more of a reason to drop that format =P<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In fact, indexed BMP might even be as efficient over the wire as GIF due to HTTP <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">Content-encoding: gzip</tt>.</div><br />Actually, 4-bit and 8-bit BMPs are compressed. I'm not making this up, BMP <em>does</em> indeed support compression (some form of RLE).</div>

