						<div class="postbody">I hear &quot;BPS&quot; and think of <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QY1G7tJ0gR4#t=10s" class="postlink">the intro to Yoshi's Cookie for Super NES</a>. It used to mean &quot;Bullet-Proof Software&quot; but apparently changed its name to &quot;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blue_Planet_Software" class="postlink">Blue Planet Software</a>&quot; in 1996 when Henk Rogers moved it to Hawaii in the process of establishing The Tetris Company. That and <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qQNnJQIPHV4" class="postlink">Pipe Dream</a>, inspiration for half the <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HackingMinigame" class="postlink">hacking minigames</a> out there.<br /><br />Someone needs to make a Yoshi's Cookie hack that just changes the B on the logo screen to an I, then distribute it exclusively as a .bps patch.</div>

